&lt;p&gt;Harvard Book Store is pleased to welcome essayist JOHN D'AGATA and erstwhile fact-checker JIM FINGAL for a discussion of their brilliant new book, The Lifespan of a Fact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How negotiable is a fact in nonfiction? In 2003, an essay by John D&amp;rsquo;Agata was rejected by the magazine that commissioned it due to factual inaccuracies. That essay&amp;mdash;which eventually became the foundation of D&amp;rsquo;Agata&amp;rsquo;s critically acclaimed About a Mountain&amp;mdash;was accepted by another magazine, The Believer, but not before they handed it to their own fact-checker, Jim Fingal. What resulted from that assignment was seven years of arguments, negotiations, and revisions as D&amp;rsquo;Agata and Fingal struggled to navigate the boundaries of literary nonfiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book reproduces D&amp;rsquo;Agata&amp;rsquo;s essay, along with D&amp;rsquo;Agata and Fingal&amp;rsquo;s extensive correspondence. What emerges is a brilliant and eye-opening meditation on the relationship between &amp;ldquo;truth&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;accuracy&amp;rdquo; and a penetrating conversation about whether it is appropriate for a writer to substitute one for the other.&lt;/p&gt;</description><event_hosts><event_hosts_item><member_name>Steve Gluck</member_name><member_id>2864884</member_id></event_hosts_item></event_hosts><maybe_rsvp_count>0</maybe_rsvp_count><waitlist_count>0</waitlist_count><updated>1334621619000</updated><rating><average>0.0</average><count>0</count></rating><group><who>Citizens of the World</who><join_mode>open</join_mode><urlname>Cambridge-Moveable-Feast</urlname><id>370532</id><group_lat>42.3899993896</group_lat><group_lon>-71.1299972534</group_lon><name>The Cambridge Moveable Feast</name></group><yes_rsvp_count>4</yes_rsvp_count><created>1333583991000</created><visibility>public</visibility><name>The Lifespan of a Fact</name><id>59296962</id><headcount>0</headcount><utc_offset>-14400000</utc_offset><time>1334617200000</time><event_url>http://www.meetup.com/Cambridge-Moveable-Feast/events/59296962/</event_url></item>